Path: godot/tutorials/3d/resolution_scaling.rst
Summary: Explains the purpose and benefits of resolution scaling in 3D rendering for improving GPU performance.
Resolution scaling is a technique used to improve GPU performance in modern games by rendering scenes at a resolution lower than the native display resolution. This is particularly useful in GPU-bound scenes, especially on mobile devices with limited performance and power budgets. While resolution scaling can significantly boost performance, it should not be seen as a complete substitute for lowering graphics settings. Developers should consider offering both resolution scaling options and graphics settings in their game menus.

Note: Resolution scaling is not currently supported for 2D rendering but can be simulated using the viewport stretch mode.
---CHUNK---
