Path: godot/tutorials/3d/resolution_scaling.rst
Summary: Explains why decreasing resolution scale might not improve performance and suggests alternative bottlenecks.
If performance doesn't increase much when decreasing resolution scale to a value like 0.5, it likely means the performance bottleneck is elsewhere in your scene. For example, your scene could have too many draw calls, causing a CPU bottleneck to occur. Likewise, you may have too many graphics effects enabled for your GPU to handle (such as SDFGI, SSAO or SSR). See the performance tutorials for more information.